main event: A military report describes the sighting of 9 unidentified blue objects with varying brightness and a light red halo flying together at medium to high altitudes.
interesting points: The objects were acquired by radar at the Norfolk radar station,The objects displayed a random flight pattern but mostly moved east, southeast, and south,They were reported to be the size of first and second magnitude stars,The weather conditions during the sighting were cloudy with wind and sea motion,The reliability of the source of the sighting was evaluated as probably good.
